# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Types:
#   feat:     New feature (→ MINOR version)
#   fix:      Bug fix (→ PATCH version)
#   perf:     Performance improvement (→ PATCH version)
#   refactor: Code refactoring (→ PATCH version)
#   docs:     Documentation only (no release)
#   style:    Code style/formatting (no release)
#   test:     Adding tests (no release)
#   chore:    Maintenance (no release)
#   ci:       CI/CD changes (no release)
#   build:    Build system changes (no release)
#
# Breaking changes:
#   feat!:    Breaking change (→ MAJOR version)
#   BREAKING CHANGE: in footer (→ MAJOR version)
#
# Examples:
#   feat(consumer): add JSON output mode
#   fix(producer): handle network errors gracefully
#   feat!: redesign configuration file format
#   docs: update README with examples
#
# Scope examples: producer, consumer, config, cli, schema
